4  Covariance Data                                                4040 1451
==================                                                4040 1451
                                                                  4040 1451
   The covariance data was taken from the 90Zr evalaution in the  4040 1451
COMMARA-2.0 library [6].                                          4040 1451
  In thermal and resolved resonance region we made use of the     4040 1451
covariance formalism based on the kernel approximation along      4040 1451
with estimates provided by S.F. Mughabghab.                       4040 1451
  In fast neutron region up to 20 MeV covariance estimates were   4040 1451
calculated using the nuclear reaction code EMPIRE and the         4040 1451
Bayesian code KALMAN. The KALMAN code along with selected         4040 1451
experimental data was used to determine the correlation matrix    4040 1451
of the model parameters. Furthermore, additional parameters       4040 1451
scaling total and absorption cross sections were included to      4040 1451
prevent the unrealistic drop in the cross-section uncertainties   4040 1451
and, in some instance, to cover the spread of the experimental    4040 1451
data. In the case of 95-Zr, for which central value of the cross  4040 1451
sections calculated by EMPIRE considerably differed from those    4040 1451
in ENDF/B-VII.0 evaluations, we applied dispersion analysis. For  4040 1451
all zirconium isotopes the total cross-section uncertainties      4040 1451
were computed as the sum of elastic, inelastic, (n2n), and        4040 1451
capture.                                                          4040 1451
